In the development of a new Policy/Procedure, the Designated Lead:
Drafts or coordinates the drafting of the proposed new or amended Policy/Procedure using appropriate Template prescribe in Executive Policy EP 2.201,Systemwide Policies and Procedures and Administrative Procedure AP 2.201, New or Amended Policies and Procedures;
Consults with members of the Policy Advisory Committee, i.e., designated system office staff members (System Office Designees have access to Policy Advisory Committee members), on Policy/Procedure draft to ensure that other system office perspectives and concerns are addressed in the draft policy;
Consults, as appropriate, with internal constituency groups, e.g., Fiscal Administrators (in collaboration with the Financial Management Office as part of quarterly meetings of FAs or by other distribution mechanisms), Personnel Officers (in collaboration with the Office of Human Resources as part of quarterly meetings of POs or by other distribution mechanisms), All Campus Council of Faculty Senate Chairs (ACCFSC), Student Caucus, etc.;
Request distribution by the responsible VP of final draft form Policy/Procedure to VPs and University Chancellors for consultation purposes (or with permission of the VP distributes the final draft on behalf of VP)
Initiates union consultations, as appropriate, in collaboration with the Office of Human Resources
Prepares and submits to the System Office Designee: (a) final form Policy/Procedure, (b) Microsoft Word Track Change version if an amendment to a Policy/Procedure is involved and (c) an Action Request to System Office Designee with system administrator access to the Policy and Procedures Information System a Action Request that provides a brief description for each of the following:  Subject, Specific Action Requested, Recommended Effective Date, Additional Costs, Purpose, Background (Basis, Rationale, Change (if an amendment to an existing Policy/Procedure) and Action Recommended (Note:  Contact a System Office Designee for a Action Request Template)
System Office Designee submits drafted Policy/Procedure into on-line Policy and Procedure Information System for review and/or approval.
